<subSubSection id="C3648BBDFF96FFEE289FFB4BFBA6880C" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC1D836FF96FFEE289FFB4BFB46885B" blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" box="[197,1245,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE289FFB4BFEFE885B" bold="true" box="[197,357,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread in the Palearctic region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA5C7FF96FFEE2B46FB4BFB81885B" author="Skoracka" box="[796,1050,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="Skoracka, A., Lewandowski, M. &amp; Boczek, J. (2005) A catalogue of eriophyoid mites (Acari: Eriophoidea) of Poland. Catalogus faunae Poloniae, Natura optima dux Foundation, Warszawa, Poland, 199 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Skoracka 
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE2BC9FB4BFC558858" box="[915,974,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2B86FB4BFB81885B" box="[988,1050,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; de 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA5C7FF96FFEE2C13FB4BFB4A885B" author="Lillo" box="[1097,1233,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="de Lillo, E. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Eriophyoidea. In: W. Magowski (ed.) Fauna Europaea: Acariformes. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, http: // www. faunaeur. org" type="book" year="2004">
Lillo, 
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2CCBFB4BFB4A885B" box="[1169,1233,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC1D836FF96FFEE289FFAA6FBA6880C" blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE289FFAA6FE258866" bold="true" box="[197,446,1305,1331]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">Relation to the host.</emphasis>
Gall-making: it causes irregularly shaped pustules raised on both leaf surfaces, often reddish on the upper side, yellow-green on the under side with an oval opening.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3648BBDFF96FFEE289FFADBFDFD88BB" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC1D836FF96FFEE289FFADBFDFD88BB" blockId="8.[151,1436,1193,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE289FFADBFEA5882B" bold="true" box="[197,318,1380,1406]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
Recorded once by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA5C7FF96FFEE2A7EFADBFCED882B" author="Bagnall" box="[548,886,1380,1406]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="Bagnall, R. S. &amp; Harrison, J. W. H. (1928) A Catalogue of the British Eriophyidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 10 (2), 427 - 445." type="journal article" year="1928">
Bagnall and Harrison (
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2B6AFADBFCF6882B" box="[816,877,1380,1406]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="1928.0">1928</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C7EA3B5FF96FFEE2BF9FADBFBEF882B" authority="L. No" authorityName="L. No" box="[931,1140,1380,1406]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatilis">
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE2BF9FADBFC2E8828" box="[931,949,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90A0424FF96FFEE2B9FFADBFBBC8828" box="[965,1063,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="23">saxatilis</emphasis>
L. No
</taxonomicName>
further collection details were given, only references to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA5C7FF96FFEE2A53FA35FD2C88F1" author="Nalepa" box="[521,695,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="Nalepa, A. (1898) Eriophyidae (Phytoptidae). Das Tierreich. Eine Zusammenstellung und Kennzeichnung der rezenten Tierformen. 4 Liefrung. Acarina, Berlin: ix + 74 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Nalepa (
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2A34FA35FD3588F1" box="[622,686,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, von Schlechtandal (
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2BEAFA35FC7588F1" box="[944,1006,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="1916.0">1916</number>
) and Houard No. 
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2C9DFA35FA9888F1" box="[1223,1283,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="3031.0">3031</number>
(
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2D49FA35FACA88F1" box="[1299,1361,1418,1444]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="1909.0">1909</number>
) were provided. The identification was made on observed damage symptoms alone and cannot be verified, an issue discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEFA5C7FF96FFEE2969FA6BFDF888BB" author="Ostoja-Starzewski" box="[307,611,1492,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" refString="Ostoja-Starzewski, J. C. (2008) Cecidophyopsis malpighianus: A case to illustrate why first records of eriophyoid mites should not be based on host symptoms alone. Cecidology, 23 (1), 6 - 10." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ostojá-Starzewski (
<number id="3DB6CA11FF96FFEE2A43FA6BFDC188BB" box="[537,602,1492,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="23" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
